  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Safety at 6 weeks follow-up</measure>
    <time_frame>6 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Safety will be assessed by incidence of Major Adverse Events (MAE), defined as a composite of the following events at 6-weeks follow-up.
All cause mortality;
End-stage Renal Disease defined as eGFR &lt; 15 ml/min or need for renal replacement therapy
Hospitalization for hypertensive crisis not related to confirmed non-adherence with medications as assessed by toxicological and other medical analyses and testing.
OR
- New renal artery stenosis &gt; 70% confirmed by angiography within 6 months of randomization</description>
